CC   -!- FUNCTION: Regulates the biosynthesis of the extracellular matrix and
CC       the biofilm formation (PubMed:19363116, PubMed:23646920). Activates the
CC       transcription of the matrix biosynthesis operons eps and tapA-sipW-
CC       tasA. Also activates expression of the opuA operon, involved in
CC       osmoprotection. Acts by binding specifically to the promoter region of
CC       the target genes (PubMed:23646920). Acts in parallel to the pathway
CC       that governs SinR derepression (PubMed:19363116, PubMed:23646920).
CC       Required for endosporulation (PubMed:23396918).
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:19363116, ECO:0000269|PubMed:23396918,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:23646920}.
CC   -!- DEVELOPMENTAL STAGE: Expressed in the forespore during sporulation.
CC       {ECO:0000269|PubMed:23396918}.
CC   -!- DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE: Mutation impairs pellicle formation, complex
CC       colony architecture and motility inhibition in a sinR mutant background
CC       (PubMed:19363116). Mutant is defective in biofilm formation and also
CC       shows a delay in spore formation during biofilm formation
CC       (PubMed:23396918). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:19363116,
CC       ECO:0000269|PubMed:23396918}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the RemA family. {ECO:0000255|HAMAP-
CC       Rule:MF_01503, ECO:0000305}.
